{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"REBAR-DEBUG DIAGNOSIS (2026-07-21)\n\nReproduced on current origin/main: open task count=2, open story count=35, but --type=task,story count=0.\n\nRoot cause: src/rebar/_engine_support/reads_cli.py passes the entire --type value through as one string. src/rebar/reducer/_filters.py applies match_predicate(..., \"type\", \"eq\", type_filter), so \"task,story\" is treated as one impossible ticket type. Unlike status/priority/tag paths, no CSV normalization or set-membership predicate exists. The list help also advertises only a singular type.\n\nMinimal corrective seam: parse type CSV once at the query boundary, filter by membership with OR semantics across CLI/library parity, document the syntax, and add an interface regression asserting the union plus single-type backward compatibility.\n\nNo code changed during this diagnostic run."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784653296604360001,"uuid":"08805a72-7cd2-45f6-9e00-423bba58c334"}